&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SPECIALTY DOCTOR – Elderly Care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary range: £41,158 - £76,751 (dependent upon previous experience)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contracted hours: 10 Programmed Activities &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tenure&lt;/strong&gt;: Fixed Term 2 Years (with view to extend)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Medicine Division is seeking a motivated and enthusiastic individual for this additional post to work Senior Middle grade level in Care of the Elderly Medicine which will enable improved middle grade support following an expansion in consultant numbers and to improve Frailty, Ortho-geriatrics and Peri-operative care of surgical patients services&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The care of the elderly department is well established department which provides acute geriatrics, Parkinson&#39;s disease, Falls, Frailty, Dementia and mental health, Ortho-Geriatrics and POP services. The post holder will work alongside Geriatrics Consultants supported by junior doctors; International Training Fellow; Specialty Training Registrars (StR) and Clinical Nurse Specialists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team provides 7 day consultant led ward rounds (including regular weekend ward rounds) in Acute Geriatrics ward, Geriatrics short stay ward, Ortho-Geriatrics as well as Frailty Assessment Unit - including all Bank Holidays. The unit also provides cover to step down beds in a care home and community geriatrics services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
